message.entry:
You just called IMTRANSFORM with a pure translation. The output image will be the same as the input image unless you specify ''XData'' and ''YData'' values in your call to IMTRANSFORM. For example, if you want the output to be the same size as the input revealing the translation relative to the input image, call IMTRANSFORM like this:

 B = IMTRANSFORM(A,T,''XData'',[1 size(A,2)],''YData'',[1 size(A,1)])

IMTRANSFORM has increased the scale of your output pixels in X-Y space to keep the dimensions of the output image from getting too large. This automatic scale change will be removed in a future release.
To ensure that output pixel scale matches input pixel scale specify the ''XYScale'' parameter. For example, call IMTRANSFORM like this:

 B = IMTRANSFORM(A,T,''XYScale'',1)
''UData'' or ''VData'' is inconsistent with size(A).
Internal problem: unrecognized property: {0}.
If either ''XData'' or ''YData'' is specified, then both must be specified.
XData and YData could not be automatically determined. Try specifying XData and YData explicitly in the call to IMTRANSFORM.
A must be a nonsparse numeric array.
Second input argument must be a valid TFORM structure.
Unrecognized interpolation option: ''{0}''
Ambiguous interpolation option: ''{0}''.
INTERP must be ''nearest'', ''linear'', ''cubic'', or a valid resampler as returned by MAKERESAMPLER.
Property names must be a string.
Unrecognized property name: ''{0}''.
Ambiguous property name: ''{0}''.
Invalid size for ''FillValues''.
''UData'' must be a real, double, 1-by-2 vector.
''UData'' must not contain NaN or Inf.
''UData'' elements cannot be equal unless A has only one column.
''VData'' must be a real, double, 1-by-2 vector.
''VData'' must not contain NaN or Inf.
''VData'' elements cannot be equal unless A has only one row.
''XData'' and ''YData'' must be real, double, 1-by-2 vectors.
''XData'' and ''YData'' must not contain NaN or Inf.
''Size'' must be real double row vector.
''Size'' must have either 2 or ndims(A) elements.
''Size'' must equal size(A) in the 3rd and higher dimensions.
''Size'' must not contain NaN or Inf.
''Size'' must contain nonnegative integers.
''XYScale'' must be a real, double, 1-by-1 or 1-by-2 vector.
''XYScale'' must not contain NaN or Inf.
''XYScale'' must contain positive values.
